<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>This has me curious. I wonder to what extent they mean dynamic</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
EQ2 most likely has virtual spaced boss-type encounters.  So when you fight through lower guk and get the key or whatever to enter the inner sanctum of the ghoul lord, when your group clicks on his doorway, you are ported into your own copy of the ghoul lord's bedroom where you can proceed to kill him without worrying if he's camped or not.  If you go back, he's dead until the 'ghoul lord timeout' has passed.  <br>
<br>
The preceeding is an example only to illustrate the concept.<br>
<br>
The advantages of such dynamic areas are that they can limit the number of people that can go in (and technically limit the level of people that go in), and therefore be able to much better control the level of challenge, and therefore be able to have encounters give rewards based on relative challenge level, rather than falling into the fallacy that if an NPC requires 40 people to kill, it's necessarily &quot;more challenging&quot; than one that requires 6.<br>
<br>
If EQ2 doesn't, then they're well behind the curve on MMORPG gameplay technology.<br>
<br>
However one of the biggest issues with EQ1 was that players are cowards and tended to bring overwhelming force where it wasn't necessary, thereby trivializing encounters.  Dynamic areas let the designers say &quot;this encounter is intended for 6 level 25 players, and no more&quot; and give it a reward they wouldn't be able to give it in EQ1, because in EQ1, people would bring 12 characters to it and trivialize the thing.<br>
<br>
<br>
-- Hika <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=26483.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=26483.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=26483.topic&start=61&stop=61>4</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=26483.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=26483.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26483.topic&index=40><img src=http://www.graffe.com/images/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=26483.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=26483.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=26483.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=26483.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2>